Rem. 34. The nouus res, thing3 spes, hope ς fides, saith, have e short in the genitive and dat. sing. (re'i, spei. fidei).

Rem. 35. Only dies and res form a complete plural. All the other nouns of this de- elension form either no plural at all, as pernicies, destruction ; planities, a plain ; fides, etc.), or only the nominative and accusative (as spes).

50. The nouns of the fifth declension are feminine, except meridies,

midday, and the plural of dies, which are masculine. In the singular dies is used either as masculine or feminine.
